text.section:
Prior to dismissal, a classified employee with status shall be notified in writing of the intent to dismiss him. The notice shall also state:
The specific reasons for dismissal including:
The statutory or regulatory violation;
The specific action or activity on which the intent to dismiss is based;
The date, time, and place of such action or activity; and
The name of the parties involved;
That the employee has the right to appear personally, or with counsel if he has retained counsel, to reply to the head of the cabinet or agency or his designee; and
Whether the employee is placed on administrative leave by the appointing authority with pay upon receiving the intent to dismiss letter prior to the agency's final action.

If the cabinet or agency head or his designee determines that the employee shall be dismissed or otherwise penalized, the employee shall be notified in writing of:
The effective date of his dismissal or other penalization;
The specific reason for this action, including:
The statutory or regulatory violation;
The specific action or activity on which the dismissal or other penalization is based;
The date, time, and place of the action or activity; and
The name of the parties involved; and
That he may appeal the dismissal or other penalization to the board within sixty (60) days after receipt of this notification, excluding the day he receives notice.

A classified employee with status who is demoted, suspended, or otherwise penalized shall be notified in writing of:
The demotion, suspension, or other penalization;
The effective date of the demotion, suspension, or other penalization;
The specific reason for the action including:
The statutory or regulatory violation;
The specific action or activity on which the demotion, suspension, or other penalization is based;
The date, time, and place of the action or activity; and
The name of the parties involved; and
That he or she has the right to appeal to the board within sixty (60) days, excluding the day that he or she received notification of the personnel action.
